Text: It's the latest release and it still works, so why bother about a date?

Uh.. Because pretty much ALL of that software is out of date!

Bug fixes, features added, blah, blah, blah.  Personally I'd stay clear of this, it's WAY to old.

I think superdisc still has one of the better tools/interfaces for changing harddrives and other related tasks. 

But for additional xbox applications I would probably look somewhere else indeed.

Consider it a "Resque disc" rather than an up-to-date software installer. ;)
